The paper focuses on real-time object detection for self-driving vehicles using lidar temporal data, which falls under the robotics (cs.RO) and computer vision (cs.CV) domains. The use of spiking neural networks (SNN) and spiking-CNNs (SCNN) also suggests a potential overlap with the machine learning (cs.LG, cs.NE) and artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-categories.
